        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 12 at 4:05PM EDT until July 12 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of western North Carolina, including the
following county, Burke.

* WHEN...Until 500 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 402 PM EDT, The gage along Hunting Creek showed that the
creek had crested and was falling.  Areas of high water
throughout greater Morganton will also be slowly receding as
rain had come to an end.  As a reminder, please never attempt
to cross a flooded road!

This advisory will expire on schedule at 5 pm.

- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Morganton, Valdese, Salem, and Drexel.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
